  "text": "We screened a total of 93,740 bp of genomic DNA, of which 42,022 bp was coding sequence and 51,718 bp corresponded to adjacent noncoding regions. We identified 48 variants (Table 1) . We also identified a 4-bp deletion within noncoding sequence in OAS3 and a variablenumber tandem decameric repeat in the gene P-selectin glycoprotein ligand 1, or SELPG, previously described by Afshar-Kharghan et al. [CITATION_1] . All of the sequence variants detected and described here either did not segregate with disease within these pedigrees or were shown to be common polymorphisms.",
